            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-dl-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><div>&nbsp;</div><article class="media media--type-image media--view-mode-default" title="Changhyun Choi">
  
      
            <div class="field field--name-field-media-image field--type-image field--label-hidden field__item">  <img loading="lazy" src="/sites/choice.umn.edu/files/files/media/cchoi.jpg" width="118" height="157" alt="Changhyun Choi" title="Changhyun Choi" typeof="foaf:Image">

</div>
      
  </article>
<h4>Changhyun Choi (PI) <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/g5kvvx6e2f8tbcfb6uucl/cv_cchoi.pdf?rlkey=kcgc04pjtkos3ruuft93axy0q&amp;dl=0">CV</a></h4><p><strong>Phone</strong>:&nbsp;+1-612-625-7870<br><strong>Email</strong>: <img src="/sites/choice.umn.edu/files/2022-06/email_0.png" alt><br><strong>Office</strong>: Keller Hall 5-157<br><strong>Mailing address</strong>:&nbsp;5-157 Keller Hall, 200 Union St. SE, Minneapolis, MN 55455, USA</p><p><strong>Bio</strong>:&nbsp;Changhyun Choi is an Associate Professor in the&nbsp;<a href="https://ece.umn.edu/">Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering</a>&nbsp;at the&nbsp;<a href="https://twin-cities.umn.edu/">University of Minnesota (UofM), Twin Cities</a>. Before joining the UofM, he was a Postdoctoral Associate in the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.csail.mit.edu/">Computer Science &amp; Artificial Intelligence Lab (CSAIL)</a>&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href="http://www.mit.edu/">Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)</a>&nbsp;working with&nbsp;<a href="http://www.csail.mit.edu/user/876/">Prof. Daniela Rus</a>. He obtained a Ph.D. in Robotics at the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ic.gatech.edu/" title="http://www.ic.gatech.edu/">School of Interactive Computing</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cc.gatech.edu/" title="http://www.cc.gatech.edu/">College of Computing</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gatech.edu/" title="http://www.gatech.edu/">Georgia Institute of Technology</a>. His broad research interests are in&nbsp;<strong>visual perception for robotic manipulation</strong>, with a focus on deep learning for object grasping and assembly manipulation, soft manipulation, object pose estimation, visual tracking, and active perception. He is the recipient of the <a href="https://beta.nsf.gov/funding/opportunities/faculty-early-career-development-program-career">NSF CAREER Award</a>, <a href="https://www.sony.com/electronics/research-award-program">Sony Research Award</a>, Russell J. Penrose Excellence in Teaching Award, and <a href="https://www.icra2022.org/program/awards">ICRA&nbsp;2022 Outstanding Student Paper Award</a>.</p><h4 class="heading-3">Ph.D. Students</h4><ul><li><a href="https://hjy-u.github.io/" data-entity-type="external">Houjian Yu</a>, Ph.D. student in ECE, Sep 2020 - present</li><li><a href="https://worobel2.github.io/" data-entity-type="external">Ross Worobel</a>, Ph.D. student in CS&amp;E , Sep 2022 - present</li><li>Mingen Li, Ph.D. student in ECE, Sep 2022 - present</li><li><a href="https://hongyoungjin.github.io/" data-entity-type="external">Youngjin Hong</a>, Ph.D. student in ECE, Sep 2024 - present</li><li><a href="https://hantao-ye.github.io/" data-entity-type="external">Hantao Ye</a>, Ph.D. student in ECE, Sep 2025 - present<br>&nbsp;</li><li><a href="https://sites.google.com/view/jiachengyuan" data-entity-type="external">Jiacheng Yuan</a>, Ph.D. student in ECE (co-advised with Prof. Isler), Aug 2020 - May 2025, now applied scientist at Amazon Robotics</li><li><a href="https://www.alireza.page/" data-entity-type="external">Alireza Rezazadeh</a>, Ph.D. student in ECE, Sep 2020 - Jul 2024, now AI research scientist at Accenture</li><li><a href="https://louxibai.github.io/" data-entity-type="external">Xibai Lou</a>, Ph.D. student in ECE, Sep 2018 - May 2023, now at Amazon Robotics</li><li><a href="https://st2yang.github.io/" data-entity-type="external">Yang Yang</a>, Ph.D. student in CS&amp;E, Apr 2019 - May 2022, now at <a href="https://about.facebook.com/">Meta</a> (Facebook)</li><li>Song Liu, Ph.D. student in CS&amp;E (co-advised with Prof. He), Oct 2020 - Dec 2021, now at <a href="https://about.google/">Google</a></li><li>Hengyue Liang, Ph.D. student in ECE, Sep&nbsp;2018 - Jun 2020, now at applied scientist at Amazon</li></ul><h4 class="heading-3">Master Students</h4><ul><li>Varaha Narsimha Swamy Menga, MS student in Robotics, Jan 2024 - present<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Chase Anderson, MS student in ECE, Sep 2022 - Jul 2024, now engineer at Hewlett Packard</li><li>Nikhilanj Venkata Pelluri, MS student in Robotics, Jan 2023 - May 2024, now ML engineer at Nokia Bell Labs</li><li>Srujan Gowdru Lingaraju, MS student in Robotics, Feb 2022 - Dec 2023, now at Intl' Electronic Machines Corporation</li><li>Ross Worobel, Robotics MS, Nov 2020 - Aug 2022, now at CS&amp;E Ph.D. student</li><li>Eddie Sasagawa,&nbsp;Robotics MS, Feb 2021 - Jun 2022, now at <a href="https://www.minevisionsystems.com/">Mine Vision Systems</a></li><li>Abhinav Mehta, MS student in CS&amp;E, Sep 2019 - May 2021, now at <a href="http://nuro.ai">Nuro</a></li></ul><h4>Undergraduate Students</h4><ul><li>Sasha Hydrie, Undergraduate UROP student in CS&amp;E, Jan 2022 - May 2022</li><li>Benjamin Tyrrell,&nbsp;Undergraduate student in ECE (Senior Honor Thesis), Sep 2021 - May 2022, now at&nbsp;<a href="https://www.spacex.com/">SpaceX</a></li><li>Nickhil Gupta,&nbsp;Undergraduate student (Independent Research) in ECE, Sep 2019 - May 2020, now software engineer at AWS</li><li>Jeanine Thao, Undergraduate student in ECE (NorthStar STEM Alliance Summer Internship, UROP),&nbsp;Jun - Aug 2019, Jan - May 2020, now software engineer at Thrivent</li><li>Stephen Mylabathula, Undergraduate student in ECE (UROP, Senior Honor Thesis),&nbsp;Sep - Dec 2018, Jan - May 2019, now at <a href="https://business.oculus.com/">Facebook Oculus</a></li></ul></div>
      
